</span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531304\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531304\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qkt1665702741070.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qkt1665702741070.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qkt1665702741070.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qkt1665702741070\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                             \n Monitor the Performance of the Uniface Router\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__topic_d31388e1_d31389e1_d31390e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__p_d31391e1_d31392e1_d31393e1\">The Uniface Router Monitor shows the settings and status of the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__li_d16088e1_d16089e1_d16090e1\">Uniface Router\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__li_d16091e1_d16092e1_d16093e1\">Uniface Servers using the Uniface Router\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__li_d16094e1_d16095e1_d16096e1\">Clients using the Uniface Router\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__p_d31394e1_d31395e1_d31396e1\">Each of these has static properties that do not change during its lifetime, as well as dynamic properties that can change constantly.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__p_d31397e1_d31398e1_d31399e1\">By default, the Router Monitor’s main form displays the Uniface Router’s static properties and dynamic properties. Two other windows display dynamic lists of connected Uniface Servers and clients. A small icon with the text ‘Periodically updating’ is displayed on the main form to indicate that dynamic information is being shown.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__p_d31400e1_d31401e1_d31402e1\">To monitor the performance of the Uniface Router:</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section ul\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__section_w6705ab1b5b3_w6706ab1b5_w6707ab1\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__li_d16097e1_d16098e1_d16099e1\">To show the Uniface Router’s dynamic properties, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">URouter &gt;Show dynamic</span></span>.\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__p_d31403e1_d31404e1_d31405e1\">To display only static properties, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Hide dynamic</span></span>\n</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__li_d16100e1_d16101e1_d16102e1\">To show the Servers using this Uniface Router, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Servers &gt;Show</span></span>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__li_d16103e1_d16104e1_d16105e1\">To display dynamic state information about a Uniface Server or a client, double-click its Detail button (<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">&gt;&gt;</span>).\n <div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__note_w6708ab1b5b3b1b5b3_w6709ab1b5b3b1b5_w6710ab1b5b3b1_w6711ab1b5b3_w6712ab1b5_w6713ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The Router Monitor is listed as a client.</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qkt1665702741070__li_d16106e1_d16107e1_d16108e1\">To hide information, choose the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Hide</span> option under <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">URouter</span>, <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Servers</span>, or <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Clients</span>.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qyk1665702738023.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Router Monitor</a><p>The Uniface Router Monitor is a Uniface Windows application that you can use to fine-tune the performance of the Uniface Router while it is running.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/exm1665702529212.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Router</a><p>The Uniface Router is a multi-threaded process (urouter) responsible for interprocess communication in Uniface applications. It listens for requests from Uniface client applications and routes them to the appropriate Uniface Server, and it passes messages between various Uniface applications.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/upi1665702529312.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Server</a><p>A Uniface Server is a server-based process that handles requests for remote data and component execution that it receives from client applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531304\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531304\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Monitor the Performance of the Uniface Router Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Monitor the Performance of the Uniface Router The Uniface Router Monitor shows the settings and status of the following: Uniface Router Uniface Servers using the Uniface Router Clients using the Uniface Router Each of these has static properties that do not change during its lifetime, as well as dynamic properties that can change constantly. By default, the Router Monitor’s main form displays the Uniface Router’s static properties and dynamic properties. Two other windows display dynamic lists of connected Uniface Servers and clients. A small icon with the text ‘Periodically updating’ is displayed on the main form to indicate that dynamic information is being shown. To monitor the performance of the Uniface Router: To show the Uniface Router’s dynamic properties, choose URouter >Show dynamic . To display only static properties, choose Hide dynamic To show the Servers using this Uniface Router, choose Servers >Show . To display dynamic state information about a Uniface Server or a client, double-click its Detail button ( >> ). Note: The Router Monitor is listed as a client. To hide information, choose the Hide option under URouter , Servers , or Clients . Related Links Uniface Router Monitor The Uniface Router Monitor is a Uniface Windows application that you can use to fine-tune the performance of the Uniface Router while it is running. Uniface Router The Uniface Router is a multi-threaded process (urouter) responsible for interprocess communication in Uniface applications. It listens for requests from Uniface client applications and routes them to the appropriate Uniface Server, and it passes messages between various Uniface applications. Uniface Server A Uniface Server is a server-based process that handles requests for remote data and component execution that it receives from client applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}